{"number":57063,"title":"[Azure Generator] The generator should make sure CollectionResults types never collide names with each other","body":"In real services, we have cases that multiple list method may share the same CollectionResult type name, but they might not be returning the same stuff, which usually leads to an error.

Could we update the azure generator to ensure this would never happen? It is incorrect in the first place, never should two different pageable operations share the same collection result.

It is simple that we could construct a typespec that could trigger it in data plane as well, for instance
```
interface Foo {
op list(...);
op listAll(...);
}
```
or
```
interface Foo {
op barBaz();
}
interface FooBar {
op baz();
}
```","state":"open","html_url":"https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/issues/57063","user":{"login":"ArcturusZhang","id":10554446,"profile_url":"https://github.com/ArcturusZhang","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10554446?v=4"},"author_association":"MEMBER","labels":["Client","CodeGen"],"reactions":{"total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"hooray":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":1},"created_at":"2026-03-13T08:25:03Z","updated_at":"2026-03-13T08:25:20Z"}
